===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|ministries}}

# Government department, at the administrative level normally headed by a [[minister]] (or equivalent rank, e.g. [[secretary of state]]), who holds it as [[portfolio]], especially in a constitutional monarchy, but also as a [[polity]]
#: ''She works for the '''ministry''' of finance.''
# The complete body of government [[minister]]s (whether or not they are in [[cabinet]]) under the leadership of a head of government (such as a [[prime minister]])
#: ''The premier offered his last '''ministry''''s resignation to the monarch, and is asked to form a new one in accordance with the election results.''
# A [[ministration]]
# The active practice and education of the [[minister]] of a particular religion or faith.
# {{lb|en|Christianity}} The [[clergy]] of [[nonapostolic]] [[Protestant]] [[church]]es.
# {{lb|en|Christianity}} [[work|Work]] of a [[spiritual]] or [[charitable]] nature.
#: ''the present '''ministry''' of the Holy Spirit''

